	   <tr><td colspan=2>Although I have never had to get yelled at for a person's dying, yet, I know what you mean by feeling bad when someone in your group dies.&nbsp;&nbsp;And about overzelous tanks hehe i know about that two sometimes I have had to implement the red light green light game (I know kinda childish) so the tank will stop hauling butt out to get more and waited for my say.  Somtimes I had to pull out the pull at your own risk cards...I hate it when they fight out of my healing range but sometimes i know this is unevitable but when they do it constantly and expect to be healed when the rest of the group is near you Im sorry but your chances of being healed just went down the hole, that is unless your the only one needing the heal. I have been living in ill omen for quite some time now and i have a few times had to leave the group who needless to say were fine and go inside to find the lost puller to keep him from dying...but i will only do that if the others are good to go. Either way I will stop babbling just to say this I have two pet peaves being a cleric ONE pullers who dont ever care about the healers mana and keep pulling one after the other. TWO people who when the healer announces in melie still yell at the cleric to heal them and dont try to get whatever is on the healer off. I know somtimes there are too many to do this right away and i know this but those who are five on one and still let the cleric get pounded on while yelling for a heal...that is all =)<br><br><br>Sunari<br>Cleric 23<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
